<subSubSection id="BB62477AB8DDD8BDD3395779A893818D" pageId="4" pageNumber="61" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="6716E337392615E22D115D298421F4A1" pageId="4" pageNumber="61">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FDDDD3E6223D71479BCF8BA9B061430A" pageId="4" pageNumber="61">
The species name 
<taxonomicName id="D70B99C144DEC83138CAD6DF736A884B" lsidName="diversipunctatus" pageId="4" pageNumber="61" rank="species" species="diversipunctatus">diversipunctatus</taxonomicName>
refers to the large difference in size between general punctures of pronotum in comparison to those of elytra.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
